76561198091937424,Not Recommended,226100,29064670,Posted: 6 January,all,Subterfusilier,"This PC Steam edition is a no-frills port of their preceding Xbox edition, which becomes pretty obvious once you start playing. Menus don't store settings correctly (I have to change the resolution/aspect every time I open a new session) and a number of controls haven't been transferred across properly; most menus are still labelled with Xbox-style toggles, and some fairly important functions (like an in-game pause/settings/quit menu a la 'start' button) just aren't there.For a game that's based completely on platformer carry-and-throw, it's anyone's guess where most of the objects are going when you throw them. A step to the left or right whilst in a corridor can make items fly backwards out of your hands, straight up, pretty much anywhere but where you were actually throwing them to. 'Automation' also moves so slowly that it's often faster to walk everything around yourself.Even single-player matches are constantly interrupted by 'night' every few minutes, and multiplayer sessions (even over LAN) frequently desynchronize and drop.In short, it's an Xbox party game that's being sold as a PC adventure game."
