76561197976343809,Not Recommended,226100,17811516,"Posted: 31 August, 2015",all,Pudenfuhrer,"I've had to revisit this review.  While we had a really good session on release, this game has been less stable since.  While playable - the game has network issues as well as a few problems with the way it handles multiplayer generally which kill it's long term appeal.  While these were to be fixed with a patch - that patch never came and I must correct my review to reflect that.  If they do fix these issues then I would heartily re-recommend this game.After starting a multiplayer game there is a period 'in time' where the render and netcode feels 'tight' and together across all the players.  After a short period it will appear to restart the game and  resyncronise.  We are now out of time with each other, the game plays in a slight slow motion and the rendered screen feels behind with the state of the game on the network.  So while at 60fps the effect is of being in a laggy slow motion.  This did not occur at release quite quite as it does now.No real thought has been given to coop play.  If people join my game they do not gain the unlocks and progress that I get - this is just half finished.  The devs have said that this  would all be fixed in a patch months ago.********************** original reviewBought one copy to check the ""lag even in local coop"" - didn't have any so bought 3 copies to play with gf and brother.15 minutes later we are making soups together-  no problems whatsoever.My machine i7 GTX970, brother AMD 965 with GTX670, gf (laptop) Core2Duo GTX650m.  No lag, no frame rate issues.I seem to be the one that likes to automate the corridors with robots and work out new soup recipes, find out which sell for the most, but also to keep the variety up (if you keep making the same soup you will lose market share eventually).  Meanwhile my brother is making security arrangements and building underground ingredient farms.  Meanwhile gf is off exploring and finding new ingredients - and better sources of existing ingredients.We fell into it really naturally - I really think this is one of the best, truly co-operative games I've played in a while.  I doubt it'd be as much fun if I had to juggle ALL those roles - but playing with friends that each have a 'thing' they want to get into is wonderful.I started to give more and more direction to my team as I worked out what we needed from my soup research - and the guys really liked fulfilling those missions to find more cornbugs - or workout a better way to defend the conveyor belts so the soup doesn't backup.We haven't unlocked anything much - but we played for hours - just exploring and (for me) mapping out all the different soup combos on the first map.  Can't wait to play more.Thoroughly recommended"
